The evening air holds soft and sweet,  
A tapestry of grassy green,  
Where all the earth in silence meets,  
Beneath the glimmer of twilight sheen;  
And as the stars begin for light,  
I drift toward the evening bright.

- Dante Gabriel Rossetti
